positioning

1. static 
	- all elements are assigned this by default
	- elements show up top to bottom and left to right in the flow of the document
2. absolute
	- positions the element at specified (x,y) coordinates
	- takes the element out of the flow of the document
3. relative
	- positions the element relative to where it would show up normally in the flow
4. fixed 
	- positions the element at specified (x,y) coordinates --- relative to the browser window
	- takes element out of the flow of the document 

position: static;